2019), 010503.</p>\n<p style=\"text-wrap: wrap;\">10. <b>P.-Y. Hou*</b>, L. He*, F. Wang*, X.-Z Huang, W.-G Zhang, X.-L Ouyang, X. Wang, W.-Q Lian, X.-Y Chang, L.-M Duan. Experimental Hamiltonian Learning of an 11-Qubit Solid-State Quantum Spin Register. Chinese Physics Letters, <em>Express Letter, </em>36(10), 100303.</p>\n<p style=\"text-wrap: wrap;\">9. F. Wang, Y.-Y. Huang, Z.-Y. Zhang, C. Zu, <b>P.-Y. Hou</b>, X.-X. Yuan, W.-B. Wang, W.-G. Zhang, L. He, X.-Y. Chang, L.-M. Duan. Room-temperature storage of quantum entanglement using decoherence-free subspace in a solid-state spin system. Phys. Rev. B 96, 134314 (2017)</p>\n<p style=\"text-wrap: wrap;\">8. Jordan Cotler, Lu-Ming Duan, <b>P.-Y. Hou</b> (Major experimental contribution), Frank Wilczek, Da Xu, Zhang-Qi Yin, Chong Zu. Experimental Test of Entangled Histories. Annals of Physics Volume 387, 334-347 (2017).</p>\n<p style=\"text-wrap: wrap;\">7. <b>P.-Y. Hou</b>, Y.-Y. Huang, X.-X. Yuan, X.-Y. Chang, C. Zu, L. He, L.-M. Duan. Quantum teleportation from light beams to vibrational states of a macroscopic diamond. Nature Communications 7, Article number: 11736 (2016).</p>\n<p style=\"text-wrap: wrap;\">6. X.-Y. Chang, D.-L. Deng, X.-X. Yuan, <b>P.-Y. Hou</b>, Y.-Y. Huang, L.-M. Duan. Experimental realization of secure multi-party computation in an entanglement access to network. Scientific Reports 6:29453 (2015).</p>\n<p style=\"text-wrap: wrap;\">5. X.-X. Yuan, J.-J. Ma, <b>P.-Y. Hou</b>, X.-Y. Chang, C. Zu, L.-M. Duan. Experimental demonstration of a quantum router. Sci. Rep. 5, 12452 (2015).</p>\n<p style=\"text-wrap: wrap;\">4. J.-J. Ma, X.-X. Yuan, C. Zu, X.-Y. Chang, <b>P.-Y. Hou</b>, L.-M. Duan. Experimental observation of entanglement duality for.</p>\n<p style=\"text-wrap: wrap;\">3. C. Zu, D.-L. Deng, <b>P.-Y. Hou</b>, X.-Y. Chang, F. Wang, L.-M. Duan. Experimental distillation of quantum nonlocality. Physical Review Letters, 111, 050405 (2013)</p>\n<p style=\"text-wrap: wrap;\">2. C. Zu, Y.-X. Wang, D.-L. Deng, X.-Y. Chang, K. Liu, <b>P.-Y. Hou</b>, H.-X. Yang, L.-M. Duan. Reply to Comment “State-independent experimental test of quantum contextuality in an indivisible system. Physics Review Letters, 110, 078902 (2013)</p>\n<p style=\"text-wrap: wrap;\">1. C. Zu, Y.-X. Wang, D.-L. Deng, X.-Y. Chang, K. Liu, <b>P.-Y. Hou</b>, H.-X. Yang, L.-M. Duan. State-independent experimental test of quantum contextuality in an indivisible system. Physical Review Letters, 109, 150401 (2012) (Editor's suggestion)</p>\n<p><br></p></div>\n \n  </div>\n  \n    <div class=\"box box0 box3 aos-init\" data-aos=\"fade-up\">\n       \n         <h3 class=\"h3-5 flex\"><img src=\"../../images/h3-5.png\" alt=\"\">Openings</h3>\n                <div class=\"arc-con arc-cons1\"><p><span style=\"text-wrap: wrap;\">We welcome highly motivated students and postdocs to join our group. If you are interested in quantum computing with trapped ions or quantum simulation and quantum sensing using NV centers, we encourage you to reach out to me by sending an email along with your CV. We look forward to hearing from you!</span></p>\n<p><br></p></div>\n \n  </div>\n  \n</div>\n\n          <div class=\"box box0 box5 aos-init\" data-aos=\"fade-up\">\n            <h3 class=\"h3-5 flex\"><img src=\"../../images/h3-5.png\" alt=\"\">相关资讯</h3>\n            \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"ls33 flexjs\">\n</ul>\n\n          </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"right\">\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<script language=\"javascript\" src=\"/system/resource/js/ajax.js\"></script><script language=\"javascript\">_getBatchClickTimes('null',2110873241,'wbnews','u12')</script>\n<script>function seeContenta12(contentid,size,displayid){    document.getElementById(contentid).innerHTML = '[';    for(var i=0;i<=size;i++){        var allcontentid = contentid+(i+1);        if(allcontentid==displayid){            document.getElementById(contentid).innerHTML += \" <span id='\"+allcontentid+\"' name='\"+allcontentid+\"'